obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (30006)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915&sectionId=30006&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Oaths Act, 1969.`
  line
  line `((2) It extends to the whole of India ^1`
  line ***.
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (30007)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Saving of certain oaths and affirmations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915&sectionId=30007&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall apply to proceedings before`
  line `courts martial or to oaths, affirmations or declarations prescribed by the Central Government with respect`
  line `to members of the Armed Forces of the Union.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (30008)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to administer oaths.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915&sectionId=30008&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following courts and persons shall have power to`
  line `administer, by themselves or, subject to the provisions of sub-section(2) of section 6, by an officer`
  line `empowered by them in this behalf, oaths and affirmations in discharge of the duties imposed or in`
  line `exercise of the powers conferred upon them by law, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) all courts and persons having by law or consent of parties authority to receive evidence;`
  line
  line `(b) the commanding officer of any military, naval, or air force station or ship occupied by the`
  line `Armed Forces of the Union, provided that the oath or affirmation is administered within the limits of`
  line `the station.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the powers conferred by sub-section (1) or by or under any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, any court, Judge, Magistrate or person may administer oaths and affirmations for the`
  line `purpose of affidavits, if empowered in this behalf--`
  line
  line `(a) by the High Court, in respect of affidavits for the purpose of judicial proceedings; or`
  line
  line `(b) by the State Government, in respect of other affidavits.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (30009)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Oaths or affirmations to be made by witnesses, interpreter and jurors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915&sectionId=30009&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Oaths or`
  line `affirmations shall be made by the following persons, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) all witnesses, that is to say, all persons who may lawfully be examined, or give, or be required`
  line `to give, evidence by or before any court or person having by law or consent of parties authority to`
  line `examine such persons or to receive evidence;`
  line
  line `(b) interpreters of questions put to, and evidence given by, witnesses; and`
  line
  line `(c) jurors:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the witness is a child under twelve years of age, and the court or person having`
  line `authority to examine such witness is of opinion that, though the witness understands the duty of speaking`
  line `the truth, he does not understand the nature of an oath or affirmation, the foregoing provisions of this`
  line `section and the provisions of section 5 shall not apply to such witness; but in any such case the absence of`
  line `an oath or affirmation shall not render inadmissible any evidence given by such witness nor affect the`
  line `obligation of the witness to state the truth.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall render it lawful to administer, in a criminal proceeding, an oath or`
  line `affirmation to the accused person, unless he is examined as a witness for the defence, or necessary to`
  line `administer to the official interpreter of any court, after he has entered on the execution of the duties of his`
  line `office, an oath or affirmation that he will faithfully discharge those duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (30010)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Affirmation by persons desiring to affirm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915&sectionId=30010&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `A witness, interpreter or juror may, instead of`
  line `making an oath, make an affirmation.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (30011)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Forms of oaths and affirmations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915&sectionId=30011&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) All oaths and affirmations made under section 4 shall be`
  line `administered according to such one of the forms given in the Schedule as may be appropriate to the`
  line `circumstances of the case:`
  line
  line `Provided that if a witness in any judicial proceeding desires to give evidence on oath or solemn`
  line `affirmation in any form common amongst, or held binding by, persons of the class to which he belongs,`
  line `and not repugnant to justice or decency, and not purporting to affect any third person, the court may, if it`
  line `thinks fit, notwithstanding anything hereinbefore contained, allow him to give evidence on such oath or`
  line affirmation.
  line
  line `(2) All such oaths and affirmations shall, in the case of all courts other than the Supreme Court and`
  line `the High Courts, be administered by the presiding officer of the court himself, or, in the case of a Bench`
  line `of Judges or Magistrates, by any one of the Judges or Magistrates, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (30012)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Proceedings and evidence not invalidated by omission of oath or irregularity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915&sectionId=30012&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No omission`
  line `to take any oath or make any affirmation, no substitution of any one for any other of them, and no`
  line `irregularity whatever in the administration of any oath or affirmation or in the form in which it is`
  line `administered, shall invalidate any proceeding or render inadmissible any evidence whatever, in or in`
  line `respect of which such omission, substitution or irregularity took place, or shall affect the obligation of a`
  line `witness to state the truth.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (30013)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Persons giving evidence bound to state the truth.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915&sectionId=30013&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Every person giving evidence on any subject`
  line `before any court or person hereby authorised to administer oaths and affirmations shall be bound to state`
  line `the truth on such subject.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (30014)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915&sectionId=30014&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00014_196944_1517807320915
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Indian Oaths Act, 1873 (10 of 1873), is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, in any proceeding pending at the commencement of this Act, the parties have agreed to be`
  line `bound by any such oath or affirmation as is specified in section 8 of the said Act, then, notwithstanding`
  line `the repeal of the said Act, the provisions of sections 9 to 12 of the said Act shall continue to apply in`
  line `relation to such agreement as if this Act had not been passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
